OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1773162680
OL,3,CRape victim who accused wrong man says
OL,4,Cpolice dismissed doubts as 'trial
OL,5,Cnerves'
OL,7,FMr Malkinson, working as a security
OL,8,Fguard, was convicted, spent 17 years
OL,9,Fin jail and became the "victim of a
OL,10,Fmost terrible miscarriage of justice,
OL,11,Fone of the worst there has been",
OL,12,FManchester Crown Court heard.
OL,14,FThe rape victim is now giving trial
OL,15,Fevidence a second time, after Mr
OL,16,FMalkinson was exonerated and fresh DNA
OL,17,Fevidence linked another local man,
OL,18,FPaul Quinn, 51, to the attack, which
OL,19,Fhe denies.
OL,26,@qD@XOUsD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1773162680
OL,3,CRape victim who accused wrong man says
OL,4,Cpolice dismissed doubts as 'trial
OL,5,Cnerves'
OL,7,FThe woman, at the time in her 30s and
OL,8,Fa mother of young children, was
OL,9,Fwalking home in the early hours of the
OL,10,Fmorning in the height of summer when
OL,11,Fshe was attacked from behind.
OL,13,FShe was strangled unconscious, beaten
OL,14,Fand twice raped in a "prolonged
OL,15,Fassault" down a motorway embankment.
OL,17,FThe woman picked out Mr Malkinson at a
OL,18,F"VIPER" digital ID parade days after
OL,19,Fthe attack on July 19 2003, but at the
OL,20,Ftrial the following year, doubts crept
OL,21,Fin.
OL,26,@vD@VOUwD@HO]zD@AOUzD@GO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1773162680
OL,3,CRape victim who accused wrong man says
OL,4,Cpolice dismissed doubts as 'trial
OL,5,Cnerves'
OL,7,FBut she told the jury that police had
OL,8,Ftold her not to worry, as it was
OL,9,Fnormal to have second thoughts due to
OL,10,Ftrial nerves.
OL,12,FLisa Wilding KC, representing Quinn,
OL,13,Fsaid: "At no stage, after that day in
OL,14,F2004, did you go to the police and
OL,15,Fsay, 'I have got that wrong'."
OL,26,@uD@GOUwD@^O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1773162680
OL,3,CRape victim who accused wrong man says
OL,4,Cpolice dismissed doubts as 'trial
OL,5,Cnerves'
OL,7,FThe woman, who cannot be identified,
OL,8,Freplied: "I did. I remember one of the
OL,9,Ftrials telling one of them, I was not
OL,10,Ftoo sure it was the right man and they
OL,11,Fsaid, 'Don't worry, it's just trial
OL,12,Fnerves'.
OL,14,F"I was very naive, I was scared coming
OL,15,Finto the court. I was reassured it was
OL,16,Ffine, it was the right man.
OL,18,F"I said, 'I was not sure it was the
OL,19,Fright man' and he said it was trial
OL,20,Fnerves and a lot of people think this
OL,21,Fand it will be OK."
OL,26,@pD@JOUvD@AOUzD@AOU}D@SO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1773162680
OL,3,CRape victim who accused wrong man says
OL,4,Cpolice dismissed doubts as 'trial
OL,5,Cnerves'
OL,7,FMs Wilding continued: "Who said that?
OL,8,FA policeman?"
OL,10,F"Yes," the witness replied.
OL,12,FMs Wilding continued: "If that was
OL,13,Fright, you could have said, 'I'm not
OL,14,Fsure' but you didn't."
OL,16,FThe witness replied: "No, because I
OL,17,Fwas reassured, I got nervous and the
OL,18,Fevidence, the process of the court, it
OL,19,Fwas not just on my identification. The
OL,20,Fother things will tell whether he was
OL,21,Fguilty or not.
OL,26,@oD@WOUpD@MO]rD@AOUrD@FO]tD@WOUvD@VO]xD@
OL,26,AVOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
