CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1773162680
OL,3,CRape victim who accused wrong man says
OL,4,Cpolice dismissed doubts as 'trial
OL,5,Cnerves'
OL,7,F"I said I was unsure because I had not
OL,8,Fseen the other gentleman with glasses
OL,9,Fon, so it threw me a bit. I was
OL,10,Funsure, then reassured, it was just
OL,11,Fnerves.
OL,13,F"I was reassured that it was normal to
OL,14,Fhave second thoughts."
OL,16,FEarlier, jurors heard Mr Malkinson
OL,17,Ffirst appealed against his conviction
OL,18,Fin 2006, but this was dismissed.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUvD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
